<br>
Okay, this raid wont work without several of each.  As in I wont even bother to take us up.  I run these with the expectation that people will sign up even if nothing for their class drops there in order to support those other classes whom I assume are their friends.  I dont have a guild or any support structure to draw additional people from.  If we dont have the appropriate people signed up I'll just cancel the raid 24 hours previous and allow a different guild to take our slot.<br>
<br>
Please, use the sign up page, dont just walk in.  Not only will you be more assured of getting a slot in the raid, I'll be able to do many of the groups prior to the raid which will speed things up.<br>
<br>
I know there are a number of clerics and enchanters who are part of CoG and frequently go on our Hate raids.  So far CoG plane raids have been open to all with no points or priority given to any, except those who signed up and were bumped for whatever reason.  If needed classes continue to only go on the plane raids that benefit their own class I will have no choice but to institute a point system where people who go to a plane that doesnt drop their armor will get bonus points for armor rolls on the other plane.  I dont want to have to do this, but if thats the only way so be it.  <br>
<br>
There are lots of guilds involved in CoG.  I urge you to ask your clerics and enchanters to sign up for Fear raids just as I would ask Druids and Paladins to sign up for Hate raids.  For Fear to be successful we will need more than what we currently have.  This will benefit everyone as the raid will actually happen.  So please check with your respective guilds and see if you can scrounge up a few more people.  And have them sign up.  Otherwise, if the raid is not viable, I wont have any choice but to cancel.<br>
<br>
Kellory Silverstar <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon2.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uhaemish.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Haemish</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>CoG Founder</span><br> <font color=#8E9173>(8/19/01 10:34:38 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fcouncilofguildscogplanesraidschedule.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=182.topic&index=1>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.godwin.com/sd/haemish.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Clerics and Enchanters for PoF</span><hr size=1> One thing to remember is that the planar armour for all classes CAN drop on both planes. On Hate, all fear armour can drop off of treasure chests and on Fear, all Hate armour can drop off of Cubes. Plus, there are some cleric belts (that are tradeable) that drop on Fear as well. <br>
